{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17613881","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17613881"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:38:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:38:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16327"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16327","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16327"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9018"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116168"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9018","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9018"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16327"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98164"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"5586"},{"type":"tags","id":"7507"},{"type":"tags","id":"11191"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21455"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21460"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116168","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116168"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe conjunctiva is a thin, transparent membrane that covers the anterior surface of the eye and the inner surface of the eyelids.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the anatomical arrangement of conjunctival folds?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Plica semilunaris and caruncle at lateral aspect","Limbus and caruncle at lateral aspect","Plica semilunaris and limbus at medial aspect","Limbus and caruncle at lateral aspect","Plica semilunaris and caruncle at medial aspect"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eplica semilunaris and caruncle are located at the medial aspect\u003C/strong\u003E of the eye. The plica semilunaris is a crescent-shaped fold of conjunctiva that represents a vestigial remnant of the nictitating membrane found in other animals. The caruncle is a small, pink nodule that contains modified sebaceous and sweat glands.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eplica semilunaris and caruncle\u003C/strong\u003E are not found at the lateral aspect of the eye. The \u003Cstrong\u003Elimbus and caruncle\u003C/strong\u003E are not anatomically related structures as the limbus is the border between the cornea and sclera. Similarly, the \u003Cstrong\u003Eplica semilunaris and limbus\u003C/strong\u003E are not anatomically associated structures. The medial location of these structures is important for tear drainage, as they are near the lacrimal puncta and canaliculi.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The plica semilunaris and caruncle are conjunctival folds located at the medial (nasal) aspect of the eye.","The plica semilunaris is a crescent-shaped fold of conjunctiva, while the caruncle is a pink, fleshy nodule containing modified sebaceous and sweat glands."],"references":["Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Probst, L., \u0026 Tsai, J. (2024). Ophthalmology: Clinical and Surgical Principles. CRC Press","Salmon, J. F. (2024). Kanski\u0027s Clinical Ophthalmology E-Book: A Systematic Approach. Elsevier Health Sciences","Kels BD, Grzybowski A, Grant-Kels JM. Human ocular anatomy. Clin Dermatol. 2015 Mar-Apr;33(2):140-6. doi: 10.1016/j.clindermatol.2014.10.006. PMID: 25704934"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98164"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1